text: - I'm Quanteer Williams.

I'm an enterprise sales
leader in the US ISV space,

and I've been with AWS
almost a year and a half now.
I was a part of smaller companies prior
and I love the startup-type mentality.
Everyone's in, all hands on deck,

we're all passionate
about what we're doing
and doing the best for our customers.

And then I went to a large
company and got to learn more

of a different structure
in being in that company.
(dance music)

Coming here to AWS, I get
the best of both worlds.

I still get to innovate,
I still get to get closer
to impacting customers in their journeys,

and I still get a great
company to work for,

so I get to do it in my
way, and I love that.

You know, you have some companies
that once a year, you hear

about our mission, our value,
or that thing that we do.

But here at AWS, the
leadership principles are real.
We actually live it.

We talk about it in our
day-to-day, we talk about it

when we're assessing
ourselves, other people.

So if you're hungry for
that next challenge,
if you find yourself kinda spinning

and unsure of what's next for
you, what does that look like?

Start to be true to what
skills you wanna build,

what value you can bring,
and know that you would have
a company that helps accelerate that.
(dance music)
